events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 31 points, Seth Curry added a season-high 29 off the bench and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Portland Trail Blazers 111-94 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Seth Curry help Nets pull away, beat Blazers 111-94

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 25 points, 11 rebounds and eight assists, Jordan Poole pitched in 24 points off the bench and the Golden State Warriors used a 47-point first quarter to spark a 137-114 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Warriors cruise to 137-114 win over Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Ivica Zubac had the best game of his six-year NBA career on Sunday afternoon. Yet, the Los Angeles Clippers center was frustrated after picking up his sixth foul late in the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zubac scores 31, pulls down 29 boards; Clippers beat Pacers

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 14 of his 32 points in the third quarter, Caleb Martin added 20 points and the Miami Heat snapped a seven-game road losing streak with a 106-98 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo has 32 points, Heat rally to beat Hawks 106-98

headlines.description: — Marcus Smart laughs when he thinks about how far Jaylen Brown has come since he was a rookie.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 36, Tatum-less Celtics outlast Wizards 130-121

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 32 points, Evan Mobley added 20 and the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied late to beat the Detroit Pistons 102-94 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Mobley lead Cavaliers to 102-94 win over Pistons

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — After Ja Morant’s triple-double at Madison Square Garden on Sunday night, his father asked for his jersey.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has triple-double, Grizzlies hold on to edge Knicks

headlines.description: — Shake Milton had 29 points and seven assists, and the Philadelphia 76ers routed the Orlando Magic 133-103 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Milton, Harris lead 76ers' rout of Magic

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen's sizzling start for Milwaukee meant the Dallas Mavericks couldn't stop their recent cold spell.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen's hot start helps Bucks defeat Mavericks 124-115
